Are developers of weapons technology morally accountable for the use of the weapons they develop?;When is the use of drone strikes justified (if ever)? Consider from an intuitive, consequentialist, and/or deontological viewpoint.

When is the use of drone strikes justified (if ever)? Consider from an intuitive, consequentialist, and/or deontological viewpoint.;In 2011, the CIA intentionally killed a U.S. citizen with definite terrorism ties using a drone strike. This action had no review from the judicial branch of the U.S. government. Should it have? What dangers might result without judicial oversight?
